           SPELL=kwlan
         VERSION=0.6.3
          SOURCE=$SPELL-$VERSION.tar.bz2
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$SPELL-$VERSION
        WEB_SITE=http://sourceforge.net/projects/$SPELL
   SOURCE_URL[0]=$SOURCEFORGE_URL/$SPELL/$SOURCE
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
     SOURCE_GPG="gurus.gpg:${SOURCE}.sig"
         ENTERED=20071113
        KEYWORDS="kde wlan"
SHORT="Network manager for kde."
cat << EOF
Allows you to configure different network profiles using all encryptions
wpa_supplicant provides (wep, wpa, wpa2 etc) for wireless networks.
kwlan can connect to unencrypted networks if wpa_supplicant is not available.

kwlan can also store profiles for wired networks.

Dialup networks can be edited and connected to as well.

Systray icons show connection statistics per interface (can be disabled).
EOF
